1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:01,910
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,910 --> 00:00:03,540
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,610 --> 00:00:05,240
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:08,650 --> 00:00:09,680
So let go of her hand...

5
00:00:11,580 --> 00:00:12,580
and back off.

6
00:00:22,860 --> 00:00:24,430
You still only see me...

7
00:00:26,830 --> 00:00:28,130
as that dead woman.

8
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:31,900
You need to figure out
where your heart...

9
00:00:33,170 --> 00:00:34,270
truly belongs.

10
00:00:40,210 --> 00:00:41,210
No.

11
00:00:42,810 --> 00:00:43,950
I don't want to let her go.

12
00:00:45,580 --> 00:00:47,590
No matter what anyone says or why,

13
00:00:49,650 --> 00:00:50,890
I don't want to let her go.

14
00:01:06,810 --> 00:01:07,840
Stop it, both of you.

15
00:01:11,780 --> 00:01:15,210
All you two seem to care about
is your own feelings.

16
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:18,280
Don't you think you're being
incredibly one-sided and rude?

17
00:01:20,520 --> 00:01:24,990
I'm not getting pulled
into this ugly drama.

18
00:02:07,970 --> 00:02:10,970
Get out of my way.
Why won't you let me leave?

19
00:02:11,470 --> 00:02:13,710
I need to settle this with Hyun Jun
once and for all.

20
00:02:13,810 --> 00:02:18,180
I'm afraid you'll end up destroying
your relationship with your son.

21
00:02:18,610 --> 00:02:23,350
Calm down and talk to him later.
Much later.

22
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:27,250
And if you can,
try to accept Chloe's apology.

23
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:30,420
Accept it? Are you kidding?
I need to put her in her place.

24
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:33,090
Come on. It's pretty obvious...

25
00:02:35,390 --> 00:02:36,530
that Hyun Jun...

26
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:39,160
has feelings for Chloe.

27
00:02:39,230 --> 00:02:40,770
Feelings? Don't be ridiculous!

28
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:45,200
My poor, naive boy is just under
that vixen's spell.

29
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:48,570
Darn, my head. My head's killing me.

30
00:02:55,350 --> 00:02:56,410
Darn it.

31
00:03:06,020 --> 00:03:07,090
What was that?

32
00:03:08,460 --> 00:03:10,660
Just like you're being true
to your feelings,

33
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,860
I'm going to follow my heart.

34
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:14,870
What if those feelings aren't real?

35
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:16,940
Not real?

36
00:03:17,070 --> 00:03:20,040
You're using Chloe as a stand-in
for Baek Jin Ju.

37
00:03:22,910 --> 00:03:26,140
You couldn't get over Baek Jin Ju
for seven years,

38
00:03:27,380 --> 00:03:30,280
and now you're just jumping
to someone else?

39
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:35,790
Can you honestly say
you're truly in love with Chloe,

40
00:03:37,990 --> 00:03:38,990
not Baek Jin Ju?

41
00:03:42,030 --> 00:03:44,760
You can't, can you?
That's your answer right there.

42
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:48,870
You can't even say for certain
that your feelings are real.

43
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,570
So butt out.

44
00:03:56,740 --> 00:03:58,080
This isn't just about Chloe.

45
00:04:01,210 --> 00:04:02,750
This is no way to honor...

46
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:05,680
the late Baek Jin Ju.

47
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:39,520
Then I guess it's hard to find out
how Oh Jung Ran managed to return.

48
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:43,860
If it involved exploiting
one of Chairman Park's weaknesses,

49
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:47,130
I was hoping we could figure out
what it is and use it ourselves.

50
00:04:48,590 --> 00:04:49,590
Then again,

51
00:04:49,930 --> 00:04:54,100
considering what she went through,
she won't let her guard down easily.

52
00:04:55,530 --> 00:04:58,270
So, what's your next move?

53
00:05:04,340 --> 00:05:05,340
What's wrong?

54
00:05:06,780 --> 00:05:08,280
Did something happen
at that house again?

55
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:12,550
- What?
- You're so lost in thought,

56
00:05:12,550 --> 00:05:14,420
you're not even listening to me.

57
00:05:14,990 --> 00:05:17,860
Don't tell me Oh Jung Ran's nasty remarks
got to you again.

58
00:05:19,790 --> 00:05:20,790
That's not it.

59
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:23,800
Her insults don't bother me
in the slightest.

60
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:27,870
What about Choi Yu Na?

61
00:05:28,270 --> 00:05:31,700
Do you think she'll just let herself
be kicked out without a fight?

62
00:05:31,870 --> 00:05:34,910
Hard to say.
For now, she's holed up at home.

63
00:05:35,340 --> 00:05:37,180
But President Kim Myung Hui
paid her a visit.

64
00:05:37,910 --> 00:05:39,580
President Kim?

65
00:05:40,310 --> 00:05:41,310
What for?

66
00:05:41,710 --> 00:05:43,010
I couldn't find that out.

67
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:45,880
In any case, I have someone
keeping an eye on Choi Yu Na,

68
00:05:45,980 --> 00:05:48,750
so we'll know the moment
something happens.

69
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:51,190
Don't worry too much.

70
00:05:58,230 --> 00:05:59,430
Are you kidding me?

71
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:02,830
If something like that happened,
you should've told me right away!

72
00:06:03,270 --> 00:06:06,340
Were you just going to hide it
if I hadn't seen your swollen face?

73
00:06:08,010 --> 00:06:10,340
This is exactly why
I didn't tell you.

74
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:12,080
It was just a slap.

75
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,910
It must have hurt.

76
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:15,880
I could tell from here it hurt.

77
00:06:16,980 --> 00:06:21,490
I'm going to tear Oh Jung Ran
and Park Tae Ho to shreds.

78
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:26,660
How can you be smiling right now?

79
00:06:28,330 --> 00:06:29,360
Well,

80
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:32,030
it reminded me how lucky I am
to have you as a friend.

81
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:36,430
You have no idea
how upsetting this is.

82
00:06:37,740 --> 00:06:40,440
It's okay. It wasn't all bad.

83
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:42,610
As painful as it was,

84
00:06:43,110 --> 00:06:45,310
I was able to take
another step forward.

85
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:48,110
I met Ms. Choi and laid the bait.

86
00:06:48,850 --> 00:06:50,310
You met with Ms. Choi?

87
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:54,390
I thought we agreed to be careful
with the Temi Bio issue for now.

88
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:57,320
What if Chairman Park finds out
and comes after you again?

89
00:06:57,690 --> 00:07:00,060
I can't just live my life
the way Chairman Park wants.

90
00:07:00,730 --> 00:07:03,160
To beat Oh Jung Ran
and the chairman,

91
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,830
I have to take risks.

92
00:07:05,030 --> 00:07:07,930
More importantly,
this is about Temi Bio.

93
00:07:08,130 --> 00:07:10,000
If there's a secret,
I have to find it.

94
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:14,540
So? What was the bait?

95
00:07:15,570 --> 00:07:16,570
Oh Jung Ran.

96
00:07:17,580 --> 00:07:20,680
Since she used the bribery ledger
to get back in,

97
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:24,350
you figured Ms. Choi could play
the Temi Bio card again.

98
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:25,780
Yes.

99
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:28,790
If Ms. Choi can make
the chairman budge,

100
00:07:29,150 --> 00:07:31,090
then one thing is clear.

101
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:34,960
There's a secret related
to Temi Bio.

102
00:07:36,890 --> 00:07:38,330
Where are you with Eunhwa Trading?

103
00:07:38,730 --> 00:07:40,630
The thing is, the painting...

104
00:07:49,310 --> 00:07:50,610
The mood in here is tense.

105
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:52,510
Should I come back later?

106
00:07:52,910 --> 00:07:56,610
Not at all. It was nothing serious.

107
00:07:56,610 --> 00:08:00,220
I was just briefing the president
on our new product.

108
00:08:00,850 --> 00:08:03,960
The new product must be
the water purifier.

109
00:08:04,690 --> 00:08:08,430
It's not a regular water purifier
but an alkaline water ionizer.

110
00:08:09,590 --> 00:08:10,630
Here.

111
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:16,600
You know how improving your water
can benefit your health.

112
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:20,000
Exercise, diet, and supplements.
Those are all great,

113
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,040
but the water you drink every day
is more important.

114
00:08:23,810 --> 00:08:27,110
I'll make sure one is at the office,
so here.

115
00:08:27,780 --> 00:08:30,350
Drink this at home every day
for your health, too.

116
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,790
It's crisp and smooth.

117
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:40,660
Then you can finish it
on your way out.

118
00:08:40,990 --> 00:08:42,360
Why don't we head out?

119
00:08:43,660 --> 00:08:44,660
Take care.

120
00:08:45,930 --> 00:08:46,930
Shall we?

121
00:08:54,070 --> 00:08:57,110
The side dishes are getting worse.

122
00:08:57,510 --> 00:08:58,740
Unbelievable.

123
00:08:58,980 --> 00:09:02,010
With both the father
and daughter out of work,

124
00:09:02,010 --> 00:09:03,050
what do you expect?

125
00:09:03,050 --> 00:09:04,280
We have to be frugal.

126
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:05,780
Stop complaining and just eat.

127
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:13,020
So, what did you and President Kim
talk about yesterday?

128
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:17,160
I begged her to give you a break.

129
00:09:17,460 --> 00:09:18,930
Didn't she ask you to come back?

130
00:09:18,930 --> 00:09:19,930
You begged?

131
00:09:21,170 --> 00:09:23,630
Do you mean you even groveled
to President Kim?

132
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:25,170
Come on.

133
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,670
To change the chairman's mind...

134
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:30,110
If anyone's changing his mind,
it'll be me.

135
00:09:31,180 --> 00:09:35,110
Please, stop groveling to everyone.
Have some self-respect.

136
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:38,120
I'll get back in on my own terms,
with my head held high.

137
00:09:39,850 --> 00:09:41,720
- What the...
- Unbelievable.

138
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:44,790
- Who does that brat take after?
- Seriously?

139
00:09:44,860 --> 00:09:46,890
Why is she so testy?

140
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:51,100
(Adele)

141
00:09:57,070 --> 00:10:00,170
Ms. Oh got back in
by leveraging her bribery ledger,

142
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:05,910
but your Temi Bio card
doesn't seem to have worked.

143
00:10:06,380 --> 00:10:08,880
Apparently,
the bribery ledger worked.

144
00:10:09,710 --> 00:10:11,880
The recording pen Chairman Park has.

145
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:14,320
The bribery ledger...

146
00:10:15,090 --> 00:10:16,190
his wife supposedly has.

147
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:21,090
I need to have
some kind of leverage like that.

148
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:25,400
I need a real trump card...

149
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:28,200
that'll get my old job back.

150
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:42,310
Ms. Choi, what are you doing here?

151
00:10:46,550 --> 00:10:49,120
Leave now,
or I'll report you to the chairman.

152
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:50,250
No.

153
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:53,620
Report me, but while you're at it,
pass on a message.

154
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:02,630
Tell him I made a reservation,
so he should come.

155
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:06,100
I'm asking for one last sit-down,
and if he refuses,

156
00:11:06,770 --> 00:11:08,470
I'll call the police,
alert the media,

157
00:11:08,470 --> 00:11:10,170
and hold a press conference.

158
00:11:10,910 --> 00:11:14,710
If he wants to avoid trouble,
he should be there.

159
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,590
So, Choi Yu Na is going
to lure out Chairman Park?

160
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:39,540
Choi Yu Na is meeting Chairman Park?

161
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:40,910
Yes.

162
00:11:41,810 --> 00:11:44,510
Looks like she's finally decided
to make a move.

163
00:11:46,510 --> 00:11:49,480
Can you find out when and where
they're meeting?

164
00:11:49,610 --> 00:11:52,480
Sure.
I've already got someone on it.

165
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:54,790
It's best if we stay one step ahead.

166
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:57,090
Right. I'll go with you.

167
00:12:08,470 --> 00:12:11,570
So you're saying this painting
is at Eunhwa Trading?

168
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:16,140
Yes. I hear the CEO is a huge fan
of Seo Yi Bon's work.

169
00:12:16,940 --> 00:12:18,940
It must have been handled
through the Adele Gallery, right?

170
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:20,740
Yes,

171
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:22,510
but two things feel off.

172
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:25,480
For one, the painting didn't belong
to the gallery.

173
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:27,990
It was
from Chairman Park's collection.

174
00:12:28,490 --> 00:12:29,520
His personal collection?

175
00:12:29,850 --> 00:12:31,490
And the other thing is...

176
00:12:32,490 --> 00:12:36,690
the painting was transferred
a month before Dr. Baek's accident.

177
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,130
A month before?

178
00:12:42,030 --> 00:12:43,130
Temi Bio,

179
00:12:44,070 --> 00:12:45,640
Dr. Baek's accident,

180
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:49,270
Chairman Park Tae Ho,
and this painting.

181
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:53,780
Where do I even begin?

182
00:13:29,650 --> 00:13:30,650
Yes?

183
00:13:30,650 --> 00:13:32,050
Chairman Park just arrived.

184
00:15:09,110 --> 00:15:10,450
Unbelievable.

185
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:12,720
Choi Yu Na.

186
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:18,060
After I made myself so clear?
How dare she try...

187
00:15:19,990 --> 00:15:21,530
this pathetic little trick?

188
00:15:23,030 --> 00:15:26,930
Does she really think
she can get something on me?

189
00:16:05,970 --> 00:16:07,540
This is my last chance.

190
00:16:13,880 --> 00:16:15,380
I have to pull this off.

191
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:41,570
What do you think you're doing?

192
00:16:55,850 --> 00:16:56,850
Ms. Choi.

193
00:16:58,220 --> 00:16:59,590
You really went all out.

194
00:17:02,090 --> 00:17:05,730
Your desperate attempt
to gain leverage over me...

195
00:17:09,830 --> 00:17:10,900
is almost admirable.

196
00:17:25,350 --> 00:17:27,650
Someone who should've been
gotten rid of quietly...

197
00:17:28,890 --> 00:17:32,060
dares to keep plotting?

198
00:17:39,130 --> 00:17:41,200
I can't just let it end like this.

199
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:44,230
You told me yourself, sir,

200
00:17:44,540 --> 00:17:46,570
that I had to rise to the very top.

201
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:48,510
That it should be me,
not Baek Jin Ju,

202
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:50,910
who gets everything.

203
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:55,410
I did everything you told me to,

204
00:17:56,310 --> 00:17:58,280
but you've given me
nothing in return.

205
00:17:59,580 --> 00:18:00,680
Given you nothing?

206
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:04,390
For a nobody like you,

207
00:18:05,590 --> 00:18:08,530
I rigged the competition
and even sent you abroad to study.

208
00:18:09,390 --> 00:18:12,400
I brought you into Adele
when you had no experience,

209
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:14,000
and I made you a team leader.

210
00:18:15,430 --> 00:18:17,700
I even approved the wedding
you desperately wanted!

211
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:23,010
And yet, you were stupid enough...

212
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:25,380
to tarnish Adele Group's reputation.

213
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:26,740
And you dared...

214
00:18:28,810 --> 00:18:31,010
to get something on me...

215
00:18:31,850 --> 00:18:33,450
and hold it over my head.

216
00:18:34,850 --> 00:18:37,020
As if what happened
could take you down.

217
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:39,390
You killed Baek Jin Ju
and Baek Jun Gi,

218
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:40,720
made it look like an accident,

219
00:18:40,790 --> 00:18:43,230
and used my father
to steal Temi Bio.

220
00:18:44,630 --> 00:18:46,660
None of that is a big deal
to you, is it, sir?

221
00:18:47,330 --> 00:18:50,130
You can probably
get away with anything.

222
00:18:51,470 --> 00:18:54,240
So how does me mentioning it
even count as leverage?

223
00:18:57,410 --> 00:18:58,410
You're right.

224
00:18:58,740 --> 00:19:01,950
I don't really see that
as leverage over me.

225
00:19:03,010 --> 00:19:04,350
But...

226
00:19:05,280 --> 00:19:07,920
the sheer arrogance
of trying to strong-arm me,

227
00:19:08,320 --> 00:19:09,350
and your insolence,

228
00:19:10,850 --> 00:19:12,420
are things I can't forgive.

229
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:21,970
Do you have any regrets?

230
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:25,740
Do you regret killing
Baek Jin Ju and Baek Jun Gi...

231
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:28,810
at all?

232
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:31,280
Regret?

233
00:19:37,810 --> 00:19:40,950
That's something
for pathetic losers like you.

234
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:43,850
My choices have always been right,

235
00:19:44,150 --> 00:19:45,990
and they have always been best
for Adele.

236
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:48,690
Even killing Baek Jun Gi...

237
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:55,230
was simply the best choice
I could make.

238
00:20:05,980 --> 00:20:07,380
Well, what a shame.

239
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:16,490
I think you're about to regret this.

240
00:20:22,660 --> 00:20:24,290
With a confession like that,

241
00:20:26,030 --> 00:20:28,130
the best thing
you can do for Adele now...

242
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,170
is let me hold this over your head.

243
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:36,210
Choi Yu Na, you...

244
00:20:40,810 --> 00:20:42,450
Get her. Quick!

245
00:20:58,700 --> 00:20:59,860
Didn't she come this way?

246
00:20:59,860 --> 00:21:02,430
She did. This is the way she went.

247
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:06,270
That recorder has
Park Tae Ho's confession on it.

248
00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:08,770
- Let's split up and search.
- A recorder?

249
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:11,540
Okay. You go that way.

250
00:21:20,650 --> 00:21:22,820
My choices have always been right,

251
00:21:23,020 --> 00:21:24,990
and they have always been best
for Adele.

252
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:27,660
Even killing Baek Jun Gi...

253
00:21:30,990 --> 00:21:34,670
He'd never think
I'd be hiding here, would he?

254
00:21:36,530 --> 00:21:40,940
Just like he never realized,
I hid a second recorder.

255
00:21:46,410 --> 00:21:48,210
Now I can get it all back.

256
00:21:49,450 --> 00:21:50,710
My future...

257
00:21:53,450 --> 00:21:54,650
and Park Min Jun.

258
00:22:29,250 --> 00:22:31,190
Even killing Baek Jun Gi...

259
00:22:32,860 --> 00:22:35,730
was simply the best choice
I could make.

260
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:43,970
I apologize, sir.
She was gone in an instant.

261
00:22:44,770 --> 00:22:48,000
Looks like she planned her escape
from the very start.

262
00:22:49,940 --> 00:22:52,380
Get Choi Yu Na in here
first thing tomorrow.

263
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:53,680
Yes, sir.

264
00:22:54,610 --> 00:22:56,510
I let my guard down.

265
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:00,150
After finding these,

266
00:23:02,390 --> 00:23:04,420
I thought I had read her every move.

267
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:08,430
Darn it!

268
00:23:23,670 --> 00:23:27,280
I saw Park Tae Ho confess
with my own eyes.

269
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:31,480
He brazenly said...

270
00:23:32,620 --> 00:23:34,020
he killed my dad...

271
00:23:35,450 --> 00:23:37,120
and had no regrets.

272
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,130
I can't forgive him.

273
00:23:48,270 --> 00:23:51,100
James, I can't forgive him!

274
00:23:52,170 --> 00:23:53,270
I swear...

275
00:23:54,910 --> 00:23:56,540
I'll make him regret everything.

276
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,440
Right.

277
00:24:00,740 --> 00:24:01,750
I know.

278
00:24:02,210 --> 00:24:05,950
At least we have his confession
on tape now, don't we?

279
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:09,450
If we can get it from Choi Yu Na,
we can pursue legal action.

280
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:12,620
No. Legal punishment is pointless.

281
00:24:13,490 --> 00:24:15,460
What difference would it make
if we took...

282
00:24:15,460 --> 00:24:16,990
Park Tae Ho and Choi Yu Na to court?

283
00:24:17,990 --> 00:24:20,030
My dad is dead and gone!

284
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:24,700
Even if those two get
the maximum sentence,

285
00:24:25,340 --> 00:24:27,640
they'll still be alive, won't they?

286
00:24:30,570 --> 00:24:31,580
Those two?

287
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:34,710
I'll end them...

288
00:24:35,210 --> 00:24:36,450
my way.

289
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:38,520
Jin Ju.

290
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:42,050
I'll send Choi Yu Na
after Park Tae Ho...

291
00:24:42,890 --> 00:24:45,960
and then have him crush her.

292
00:24:47,220 --> 00:24:50,090
I'll have them
tear each other apart...

293
00:24:51,230 --> 00:24:54,100
until one kills the other.

294
00:24:55,130 --> 00:24:58,440
Jin Ju, listen.
We have evidence now,

295
00:24:58,670 --> 00:25:00,270
so at least consider
a legal approach.

296
00:25:00,670 --> 00:25:03,910
A bloody ending like that
will only leave you scarred too.

297
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:06,910
And other innocent people
could get hurt in the process.

298
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:10,210
The second Choi Yu Na comes back,
she's going to demand marriage.

299
00:25:10,450 --> 00:25:12,780
Your friend, Park Min Jun,
will get dragged into this again.

300
00:25:14,520 --> 00:25:17,720
I don't want to think
that far ahead.

301
00:25:21,460 --> 00:25:23,330
To get the ending I want,

302
00:25:25,700 --> 00:25:26,700
I'm...

303
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:30,300
prepared to do anything.

304
00:25:51,350 --> 00:25:53,520
Did I let you go too easily?

305
00:25:56,190 --> 00:25:58,330
I don't even know
how I feel anymore.

306
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:01,600
I'm sorry.

307
00:26:25,390 --> 00:26:27,220
Try them on. I'm sure they'll fit.

308
00:26:44,540 --> 00:26:45,540
I won't...

309
00:26:48,110 --> 00:26:49,710
feel guilty for doing this to you,

310
00:26:53,050 --> 00:26:54,350
and I won't let you sway me.

311
00:26:57,850 --> 00:26:58,920
No one in the Adele family...

312
00:26:59,660 --> 00:27:02,060
feels sorry for us,

313
00:27:04,330 --> 00:27:05,330
so why should I?

314
00:27:10,130 --> 00:27:11,130
No matter...

315
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:13,240
how miserable...

316
00:27:14,570 --> 00:27:15,670
you become...

317
00:27:25,850 --> 00:27:27,050
No matter how bad it gets,

318
00:27:28,180 --> 00:27:30,150
it's nothing compared
to what I've been through.

319
00:27:41,530 --> 00:27:42,600
From now on...

320
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:47,200
I...

321
00:27:50,110 --> 00:27:51,240
I won't lose.

322
00:27:53,780 --> 00:27:56,810
To Park Tae Ho, Choi Yu Na,

323
00:28:00,550 --> 00:28:01,720
and you.

324
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:07,060
I'll never lose to any of you.

325
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:35,620
(Adele)

326
00:28:35,690 --> 00:28:38,460
(Team Leader, Choi Yu Na)

327
00:28:45,230 --> 00:28:48,000
Is Ms. Choi really coming back?

328
00:28:48,830 --> 00:28:50,630
How can someone
who stole the design book...

329
00:28:50,730 --> 00:28:52,000
get reinstated?

330
00:28:57,870 --> 00:28:59,380
(Team Leader, Choi Yu Na)

331
00:29:00,810 --> 00:29:01,810
That's a good question.

332
00:29:02,450 --> 00:29:05,350
I guess we'll have to ask her
in person.

333
00:29:17,060 --> 00:29:19,800
Is Choi Yu Na really
being reinstated?

334
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:21,800
Looks like it.

335
00:29:22,100 --> 00:29:23,730
I heard it was the chairman's order.

336
00:29:23,730 --> 00:29:25,340
What is he thinking?

337
00:29:25,770 --> 00:29:27,370
I'll confirm with the chairman.

338
00:29:31,410 --> 00:29:32,410
Choi Yu Na.

339
00:29:33,180 --> 00:29:34,180
Good morning.

340
00:29:35,180 --> 00:29:36,410
It's good to see you again.

341
00:29:37,480 --> 00:29:41,080
Hey, what do you think you're doing?
How can you be back here?

342
00:29:42,050 --> 00:29:43,050
Who knows?

343
00:29:43,420 --> 00:29:45,520
Maybe it's the same way
your mom was allowed back.

344
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:46,520
You...

345
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:53,230
I bet you're all wondering
how this happened.

346
00:29:54,360 --> 00:29:57,570
They thought
I stole Chloe's design book,

347
00:29:58,430 --> 00:30:01,100
but the police investigation proved
I didn't.

348
00:30:01,540 --> 00:30:02,540
So,

349
00:30:03,970 --> 00:30:05,410
I've been reinstated.

350
00:30:23,630 --> 00:30:25,300
Are you just pretending
to be unfazed?

351
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:29,400
You look so thrilled
to have me back.

352
00:30:31,430 --> 00:30:33,140
You said you were proven innocent.

353
00:30:33,870 --> 00:30:35,510
Of course I should congratulate you.

354
00:30:36,810 --> 00:30:39,710
How about we get some tea
to celebrate your return?

355
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:43,610
I think we still have
a lot to talk about.

356
00:30:57,960 --> 00:31:00,400
Don't go spreading baseless rumors.

357
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:05,300
It's useless to insist I'm the one
who stole the design book.

358
00:31:06,940 --> 00:31:08,670
As long as the chairman is
on my side,

359
00:31:09,070 --> 00:31:10,370
I'm innocent...

360
00:31:10,940 --> 00:31:12,210
no matter what you say.

361
00:31:13,110 --> 00:31:15,650
After getting kicked out,
you made a flashy comeback...

362
00:31:16,150 --> 00:31:19,350
and boldly claimed the chairman is
on your side.

363
00:31:20,780 --> 00:31:23,090
That tells me you have dirt
on Chairman Park.

364
00:31:27,490 --> 00:31:30,830
But how long do you think
he'll put up with it?

365
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:35,700
We're talking
about Chairman Park of Adele.

366
00:31:37,670 --> 00:31:39,000
Can you really handle him
on your own?

367
00:31:41,500 --> 00:31:42,940
What are you talking about?

368
00:31:55,650 --> 00:31:56,690
And you are?

369
00:32:05,430 --> 00:32:08,330
I'm Kim Myung Hui,
the president of the Adele Group.

370
00:32:09,530 --> 00:32:12,000
I'm here to propose a deal, sir.

371
00:32:16,670 --> 00:32:17,670
How about we...

372
00:32:18,710 --> 00:32:20,110
be friends?

373
00:32:21,910 --> 00:32:25,250
I'll help you use
the leverage you have...

374
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:28,650
to your advantage.

375
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:57,180
(Pearl in Red)

376
00:32:57,250 --> 00:33:01,320
I won't stand here trembling
before you anymore, sir.

377
00:33:01,650 --> 00:33:05,990
Good. If you're that determined,
that makes this much easier for me.

378
00:33:06,490 --> 00:33:08,360
Stay out of Chloe's business.

379
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:09,390
That's enough.

380
00:33:09,460 --> 00:33:13,100
Now that Choi Yu Na is back,
your wedding will be back on, right?

381
00:33:13,330 --> 00:33:15,060
Stop worrying about Chloe
and mind your own business.

382
00:33:16,230 --> 00:33:18,230
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
